x-info.content:
These options are passed via `settings.filepondDocuments` in the Jedison init options.

Options like `acceptedFileTypes`, `labelIdle`, and `labelFileTypeNotAllowed` contain **MIME type arrays** and **HTML strings** that cannot be expressed cleanly in JSON — so the entire FilePond config is consolidated here.

---

```js
jedison({
  settings: {
    filepondDocuments: {
      allowMultiple: true,
      maxFiles: 5,
      credits: false,
      acceptedFileTypes: [
        'image/jpeg',
        'image/png',
        'image/gif',
        'image/webp',
        'application/pdf'
      ],
      maxFileSize: '10MB',
      labelIdle: 'Drag & drop photos or PDFs here or <span class="filepond--label-action">Browse</span>',
      labelFileTypeNotAllowed: 'Only images and PDFs are accepted',
      fileValidateTypeLabelExpectedTypes: 'Accepts JPEG, PNG, GIF, WebP, PDF',

      // Optional: set a server endpoint to enable real uploads.
      // When present, the editor value is set to the server-returned ID(s)
      // instead of the local filename(s).
      // server: '/upload'
    }
  }
})
```
